description:
What: Update the WHISPER_DELIVER handler in cli/src/commands.rs to display incoming DMs instead of silently treating all WhisperDeliver payloads as MLS Welcome bytes.

Currently the handler (around line 854) tries mls.join_from_welcome() on ALL WhisperDeliver payloads and drops them after mls_active=true. This must be changed to dispatch on content type.

Algorithm:
Find the WHISPER_DELIVER handler block in commands.rs. It currently looks like:
  ClientEvent::Message(notif) if notif.method == rpc_methods::WHISPER_DELIVER => {
      let p: WhisperDeliverParams = ...;
      let payload = p.payload;
      if !mls_active {
          match mls.join_from_welcome(&payload) { ... }
      }
  }

Replace the body with:
  ClientEvent::Message(notif) if notif.method == rpc_methods::WHISPER_DELIVER => {
      let p: WhisperDeliverParams = match serde_json::from_value(...) { ... };
      let from = p.from;
      let payload = p.payload;
      // Try to deserialize as ClearMessage (DM content).
      // MLS Welcome bytes are binary and will NOT parse as JSON.
      match serde_json::from_slice::<ClearMessage>(&payload) {
          Ok(ClearMessage::Chat { text }) => {
              // Incoming DM (Phase 1: pre-MLS plaintext)
              let ts = Local::now().format("%H:%M");
              let name = colored_name(&from, &nicknames, &local_names);
              println!("\r[{ts}] DM from {name}: {text}");
          }
          Ok(_) => {
              // Other ClearMessage variants (Payment, Ack, Profile) not expected via Whisper in Phase 1
              warn!("unexpected ClearMessage type in WhisperDeliver from {from}");
          }
          Err(_) => {
              // Not JSON → treat as MLS Welcome (existing behavior)
              if !mls_active {
                  match mls.join_from_welcome(&payload) {
                      Ok(()) => {
                          mls_active = true;
                          // ... keep all existing MLS activation code unchanged ...
                      }
                      Err(e) => warn!("join_from_welcome: {e}"),
                  }
              }
              // If mls_active and payload is not JSON, it is unexpected; warn and drop
          }
      }
  }

Defensive rules:
- Never deserialize payload in relay (this is CLI code only — architectural invariant maintained)
- serde_json::from_slice failure is NOT an error — it's the signal that the payload is MLS data
- Keep ALL existing MLS activation code (the Ok(()) branch and all its side effects) — do not simplify or remove
- Display with 'DM from' prefix (not same format as room messages) for clear distinction

Tests:
- Unit test: create WhisperDeliverParams with payload=serde_json::to_vec(ClearMessage::Chat{text:'hello'}), feed to handler, verify 'DM from' appears in output; oracle = independently serialized expected payload
- Unit test: create WhisperDeliverParams with payload=b'\x00\x01\x02\x03' (invalid JSON = MLS-like bytes), feed to handler when mls_active=false, verify join_from_welcome is called (can use a mock mls or just check the non-panic path)
